OL,3,CNo extra money for NHS and teacher pay
OL,4,Crises, says No 10, amid strikes warning
OL,6,FThe independent pay review body is
OL,7,Freportedly recommending increases of
OL,8,Fas much as 4% for some public sector
OL,9,Fworkers like teachers and 3% for NHS
OL,10,Fworkers, according to The Times.
OL,12,FHowever, the government has only
OL,13,Fbudgeted for a 2.8% rise for public
OL,14,Fsector workers and Downing Street says
OL,15,Fthere will be no funding beyond what
OL,16,Fwas set out in the Budget.
OL,18,FSir Keir Starmer said on Monday that
OL,19,Fno decisions had been made on the
OL,20,Frecommendations, saying "we are not at
OL,21,Fthat stage of the process".
